        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 10:31PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1030 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brent, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Heiberger, Trio, Eoline, Centreville, Ashby, West Blocton, West
Centreville, Brent, Ellards, Six Mile, and Bibb County Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
